{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Plan how deterministic proof of no-guidance-lost criterion will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f4cd9e1449f822868","fa8dcf65502be0d75"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"deterministic proof of no-guidance-lost criterion"},{"coaching":"Plan how automated verification path for CLAUDE.local.md rules will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fa1cbb96797dc641a","f847919a5cfeb874c","f7ec73e522487fbf4"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"automated verification path for CLAUDE.local.md rules"},{"coaching":"Record an ADR for AGENTS.md-as-canonical architectural decision — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f7d75c0b62ada3d6a","f6cce356036fef896"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"AGENTS.md-as-canonical architectural decision"},{"coaching":"Research prior art / OSS for per-provider AGENTS.md native-read evidence before building it custom.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["ff52efbd77ab7985f"],"move_id":"2","move_name":"prior-art research","subject":"per-provider AGENTS.md native-read evidence"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] Linux Foundation AGENTS.md governance claim will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fff3847c7ecfb8a82"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"Linux Foundation AGENTS.md governance claim"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] SKILL.md cross-provider standard provenance will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f763995329e7d5fed"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"SKILL.md cross-provider standard provenance"},{"coaching":"Propagate the revision for sibling ticket file-ordering dependencies to the child tickets.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f82524518cbf636a6"],"move_id":"11","move_name":"propagate to children","subject":"sibling ticket file-ordering dependencies"},{"coaching":"Pin down examples reference sweep coverage gap with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fe0e449c27d3197f6"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"examples reference sweep coverage gap"},{"coaching":"Plan how acceptance criteria shell-command completeness will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"acceptance criteria shell-command completeness"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":13,"blocking":0,"dropped":19,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":5,"ran":true,"references":5,"resolved":1,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":4},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":3802,"file_impact":0,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":7,"edges":6,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"fail"},"P6":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":35,"verify_lint_abstained":35},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":975,"ran":true,"status":"pass","worst_parent_child_pair_tokens":2179},"P9":{"applicable":false,"blocking":false,"file_impact":0,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":709.9,"llm_calls":22,"llm_ms":694683.3,"total_ms":695547.7,"verify_requests":22},"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":false,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":false}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["G3","G4","G6","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","F1","F4","G5","T2","T4","T5e","T7"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a CI-checkable artifact for the CLAUDE.local.md remediation (e.g., a committed CLAUDE.local.md.example showing only the local-only skeleton, or a note in AGENTS.md/CONTRIBUTING.md documenting what belongs in a local override), so the 'no guidance lost' criterion has a machine-verifiable proxy.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3","G4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"CLAUDE.local.md (git-ignored, local)\" stated in child 955c Scope","\"Proving: reviewer confirms\" for AC1 and AC2","Parent SC4 states: 'every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home in AGENTS.md or docs/'","No child provides a CI-checkable artifact proving CLAUDE.local.md's generally-applicable rules are absent","container pairing: parent + 064f-0484-2795-4ac7/073d-51d8-3e58-4b14/1d75-89cb-f37e-482e/46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508/5b01-add0-e970-44bd/6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4/955c-7a98-2485-4209"],"finding":"Child 955c-7a98-2485-4209 remediates CLAUDE.local.md, which is a git-ignored local file. All proving steps are 'reviewer confirms' with no CI enforcement. Parent SC4 ('every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home') cannot be machine-verified for the CLAUDE.local.md portion, creating a structural gap in the completion criteria.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa1cbb96797dc641a","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 955c-7a98-2485-4209","norm_id":"n8e86ceb7a111fc5e","priority":1.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["The completion verifier (parent: 'All child stories are closed and their changes are landed on main') cannot confirm SC4 for the CLAUDE.local.md half of the cleanup, since git-ignored files leave no tracked trace.","A future contributor whose CLAUDE.local.md was never remediated continues to operate with duplicated, potentially stale local rules."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Commit a `CLAUDE.local.md.example` (or `.example.local`) to the repo showing the post-remediation skeleton, which CI can check for absence of the banned project-workflow rules via a grep test.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"SC4 ('no guidance is lost in the move — every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home') has no automated verification path for the CLAUDE.local.md half. 955c's AC relies solely on reviewer confirmation ('reviewer confirms') and a trending-to-zero rg check on locally removed patterns. Since CLAUDE.local.md is gitignored, CI cannot read it, and the content-completeness check ('for each removed rule, cite the AGENTS.md/docs location in the change description') is a manual code-review step with no enforcement. The parent success criterion is not measurably satisfied in the same terms (automated, reproducible) as the CLAUDE.md half.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f847919a5cfeb874c","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 955c-7a98-2485-4209 — Acceptance Criteria; parent SC4","norm_id":"n4766ab20eadf4211","priority":1.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"In 955c, produce an explicit removal manifest (a table: removed rule | new home | verified by) as part of the change description, and cross-reference it against 6642's AGENTS.md content in the same review. This is the closest achievable substitute for automated verification given the gitignored nature of the file.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":["ISF"],"criteria":["ISF"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Session log child 955c: 'Remediate CLAUDE.local.md to machine/operator-local content only'","Plan Context: 'CLAUDE.local.md mixes genuinely machine/operator-local content with generally-applicable project rules copied from CLAUDE.md' — problem is stated","Plan AC: three explicit proving steps (AGENTS.md+CLAUDE.md, templates/AGENTS.md+test, skills rename) — none for CLAUDE.local.md","Blanket AC 'All child stories are closed' is the only coverage for 955c, whereas other children each have independent shell-command proofs"],"finding":"The CLAUDE.local.md remediation (child 955c) has no dedicated acceptance criterion or shell-command proving step in the plan's AC section, while every other major deliverable has an explicit, independently verifiable proof. The plan acknowledges the CLAUDE.local.md problem in Context but silently narrows the verification posture for this child story compared to all others.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7ec73e522487fbf4","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"n5bf4841ab3d3d6d7","priority":0.875,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["955c is marked 'closed' by its author but CLAUDE.local.md still contains non-local project rules; without a proving step the epic's AC passes while the remediation is incomplete","A reviewer confirming the epic's AC can verify all three explicit criteria by shell command but has no equivalent check for CLAUDE.local.md cleanliness"],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a concrete, in-session proving command for the 'no guidance lost' criterion — e.g. produce a migration checklist artifact (a markdown table mapping every CLAUDE.md section to its new home) and require it in the PR, or add a test that asserts no section heading present before migration is absent after.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["F1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'No guidance is lost in the move — every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home in AGENTS.md or docs/' — no corresponding AC proving command","All four ACs have explicit proving commands; this success criterion does not appear among them","ABSENCE: no diff-based or checklist-based verification is described"],"finding":"The 'No guidance is lost in the move' success criterion has no in-session, deterministic proving command, making it unverifiable. It is stated as a success criterion but is purely qualitative without a check.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4cd9e1449f822868","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Success Criteria — 'No guidance is lost in the move — every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home in AGENTS.md or docs/'","norm_id":"nefd9acf27d92c3ae","priority":0.5714,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor completes the migration and believes it is done, but drops a rule that was in CLAUDE.local.md without noticing — no test catches it.","A reviewer has no way to verify completeness in CI."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5714,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (and corresponding test or script) that verifies every substantive rule present in the pre-migration `CLAUDE.md`/`CLAUDE.local.md` is traceable to an authoritative home in `AGENTS.md` or `docs/` — e.g., a checklist snapshot, a line-diff audit script committed to the repo, or a CI step that compares a recorded rule inventory.","cohort":["E3","F4"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'No guidance is lost in the move — every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home in AGENTS.md or docs/' — named as a success criterion with no corresponding AC or test","The three AC proving commands are: `test -f AGENTS.md && rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md`, `test -f templates/AGENTS.md && make test`, and `rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l` — none checks for content completeness"],"finding":"The Success Criterion 'No guidance is lost in the move — every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home in AGENTS.md or docs/' has no end-state-observable proof in the Acceptance Criteria. The three AC shell commands verify file existence and reference removal but do not assert content completeness.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa8dcf65502be0d75","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Success Criteria (4th bullet) / Acceptance Criteria section","norm_id":"n8eebe2f060989ff1","priority":0.5714,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An agent deletes a rule from CLAUDE.md and never migrates it; all three ACs still pass and the omission is undetectable.","During review, no automated gate catches guidance silently dropped during migration."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Commit a machine-readable inventory (e.g., `docs/migration-manifest.md`) listing each rule's source and destination before migration begins; add a CI lint step that asserts every source rule appears in the manifest with a non-empty destination. AC proving command: `python tools/check_migration_manifest.py` (or equivalent).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5714,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P5"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AGENTS.md: 1d75-89cb-f37e-482e & 6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4 (no ordering edge)"],"finding":"Sibling tickets touch the same file(s) with no ordering edge.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f82524518cbf636a6","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"na0177dc3af65d74f","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a depends_on/blocks edge to serialize, or partition the file ownership.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["1 criterion line(s) bundle multiple deliverables with 'and' (split so each is independently verifiable)."],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add child 46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508 as a formal depends_on in child 5b01-add0-e970-44bd to enforce that the rename lands before the reference sweep closes.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["S6 (5b01) Scope: 'Owned by other stories (out of scope here): examples/claude-skills/...' (S5 repoints them)'","S6 AC1 proving: `':!examples'` exclusion in git grep","S6 stated dependencies: 'Depends on S1, S2, S3' — 46f8 (the rename story) is absent","Parent AC3 proving: `rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l` returns 0 — this requires both stories to have landed","container pairing: parent + 064f-0484-2795-4ac7/073d-51d8-3e58-4b14/1d75-89cb-f37e-482e/46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508/5b01-add0-e970-44bd/6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4/955c-7a98-2485-4209"],"finding":"Child 5b01-add0-e970-44bd (the reference sweep) delegates examples/ references entirely to child 46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508 (the rename story) via an exclusion in its proving command (':!examples'), but 5b01 does NOT declare 46f8 as a dependency. If 5b01 lands before 46f8, the global reference sweep will pass (examples excluded from S6's check) while stale 'examples/claude-skills' references remain, and the parent AC3 proving command `rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l` would fail.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe0e449c27d3197f6","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 5b01-add0-e970-44bd","norm_id":"ned47fdab761e76f2","priority":0.231,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["5b01 lands before 46f8: S6's CI checks pass (examples excluded), but the parent AC3 check fails. The epic is reported closed with a broken parent proving command.","Integration order is unspecified in the backlog; without a formal depends_on, a merge bot or developer could order them incorrectly."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In 5b01's ticket metadata, add '46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508' to the depends_on list alongside S1/S2/S3.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify and document AGENTS.md support status for each named provider (with version/date), and note any providers that require a parallel per-provider file (e.g., `.cursor/rules/` for Cursor, `.github/copilot-instructions.md` for Copilot) so the scope boundary is accurate.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'read natively by Codex, Cursor, Copilot's coding agent, Zed, Windsurf, Amp, Factory, Jules, Devin, RooCode, and Cline'","No per-provider documentation links or version references are cited","Cursor's documented agent context mechanism is .cursor/rules/ (MDC format), not AGENTS.md","GitHub Copilot's documented custom instructions file is .github/copilot-instructions.md, not AGENTS.md","No verification matrix or research artifact exists in the repo for this claim"],"finding":"The plan asserts AGENTS.md is read natively by 11 named providers (Codex, Cursor, Copilot's coding agent, Zed, Windsurf, Amp, Factory, Jules, Devin, RooCode, Cline) but provides no per-provider verification. Cursor's primary agent-context mechanism is `.cursor/rules/` (MDC files); GitHub Copilot's is `.github/copilot-instructions.md`. If a significant subset of these providers does not actually read a root `AGENTS.md`, the cross-vendor de-duplication premise requires per-provider shims that the plan explicitly excludes from scope.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ff52efbd77ab7985f","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Context section — '…read natively by Codex, Cursor, Copilot's coding agent, Zed, Windsurf, Amp, Factory, Jules, Devin, RooCode, and Cline'","norm_id":"ne336c0bab004f562","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Several providers in the list only read AGENTS.md in specific modes (e.g., agent mode only, not inline chat) — partial support degrades the value proposition","Cursor reads AGENTS.md as a fallback but prioritizes .cursor/rules/ — the richer MDC format supports per-file scoping that AGENTS.md cannot match, meaning teams using Cursor would lose capability","Some listed tools (Amp, Factory, Jules) are early-stage and their AGENTS.md support may be aspirational or undocumented"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Commit a lightweight ADR (e.g., `docs/adr/agents-md-adoption.md`) summarizing the AGENTS.md governance decision, provider support matrix, and migration rationale, so the architectural choice is durable and in-repo.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'See the design-of-record session log for the full research basis (AGENTS.md governance, provider matrix, OSS patterns, anti-patterns).' — the session log is external/ephemeral.","ABSENCE: No planned ADR file (e.g., docs/adr/0001-agents-md-adoption.md) appears in Scope or Acceptance Criteria.","T7 rubric: 'a new architectural decision with no ADR/doc = MAJOR'."],"finding":"The architectural decision to adopt AGENTS.md as the cross-vendor canonical standard is backed only by an external 'design-of-record session log' that is not committed to the repo. No ADR or equivalent persisted design doc is planned.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7d75c0b62ada3d6a","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Context section / Locked decisions paragraph","norm_id":"n40b6091e71214eed","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A future maintainer questions why AGENTS.md was chosen over CLAUDE.md or a different convention; the session log is inaccessible or stale, and there is no in-repo record.","A contributor wants to understand the provider support matrix (Codex, Cursor, Copilot, etc.) to evaluate adding a new one — the research exists only in an external log."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Create `docs/adr/agents-md-adoption.md` with: (1) Context (Claude-lock problem), (2) Decision (AGENTS.md as canonical), (3) Provider support matrix, (4) Consequences. Reference it from the root AGENTS.md.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7143,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a plan step (or AC) that commits an in-repo design record — an ADR in `docs/decisions/` or a `## Architecture` section in the new `AGENTS.md` — capturing the canonical-file choice, shim pattern, template+drift-guard contract, and provider-matrix rationale before the epic closes.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'See the design-of-record session log for the full research basis (AGENTS.md governance, provider matrix, OSS patterns, anti-patterns).'","No story, AC, or plan step names creating an ADR or design-doc entry in the repo.","The session log is an external artifact; future contributors working from the repo alone will find no durable rationale for the shim pattern, template contract, or provider-neutrality decision."],"finding":"The plan introduces a novel repo-level architectural decision (AGENTS.md as canonical, CLAUDE.md-as-shim pattern, template+drift-guard contract) but defers its documentation to an external 'design-of-record session log' that is not guaranteed to land in the repo; no plan step commits to capturing this decision in a durable, in-repo artifact (ADR, `docs/decisions/`, or the new AGENTS.md itself).","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6cce356036fef896","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Context section — 'See the design-of-record session log for the full research basis'","norm_id":"n1ee4a60df001a7a4","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A contributor six months later wonders why CLAUDE.md is a one-liner, searches the repo, finds no ADR, and reverts or re-duplicates content.","A new provider (e.g., a future agent harness) integration question arises and there is no in-repo record of the provider-matrix reasoning."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add one story (or a sub-task of the AGENTS.md authoring story): 'Create `docs/decisions/adr-001-agents-canonical.md` summarising: (1) why AGENTS.md over CLAUDE.md, (2) the shim pattern, (3) the template+drift contract, (4) provider support matrix.' Reference this ADR from the new AGENTS.md header so it is discoverable from first-read.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7143,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a verifiable citation (URL to the Linux Foundation body, the AGENTS.md spec, or the announcement) for the governance claim that AGENTS.md was donated to the Agentic AI Foundation; if the spec is pre-ratification, note that and qualify the provider matrix accordingly.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'AGENTS.md is now the de-facto cross-vendor standard (OpenAI 2025 → donated to the Linux Foundation's Agentic AI Foundation, co-founded by Anthropic/OpenAI/Block, Dec 2025)'","No URL, spec link, or governance document is cited in the plan","No matching reference found in docs/research/ or anywhere in the repo","The 'design-of-record session log' that supposedly contains the research basis is not linked or accessible for verification"],"finding":"The plan's entire cross-vendor migration rationale rests on the claim that AGENTS.md was 'donated to the Linux Foundation's Agentic AI Foundation, co-founded by Anthropic/OpenAI/Block, Dec 2025' — but no URL, spec document, or verifiable governance link is cited anywhere in the plan or the repo. If this governance claim is inaccurate or the spec is still a draft/proposal, the premise for preferring AGENTS.md over .cursorrules / .github/copilot-instructions.md / per-provider files is weakened.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fff3847c7ecfb8a82","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Context section — 'AGENTS.md is now the de-facto cross-vendor standard … donated to the Linux Foundation's Agentic AI Foundation, co-founded by Anthropic/OpenAI/Block, Dec 2025'","norm_id":"n042875b9c8cc1c5a","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["The Linux Foundation body or donation did not occur as described, making the standard-body argument for AGENTS.md unsupported","The spec exists but is a pre-ratification draft, meaning provider adoption is not yet required and the provider matrix is aspirational rather than current"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a `docs/research/agents-md-standard.md` note (following the repo's existing pattern) with: the spec URL, the governance announcement link, the current ratification status, and which providers have shipped verified AGENTS.md support as of the plan date — mirroring how docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md grounds its claims.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify the 'cross-provider open standard' claim for SKILL.md and either cite a governance URL or reframe it as 'an established community convention originated by obra/superpowers and adopted across several tools' to match the actual evidence.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-provider open standard)'","docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md cites SKILL.md as originating from 'obra/superpowers (skills/writing-plans/SKILL.md)' — a single GitHub repo","No governance body, spec URL, or multi-vendor adoption evidence is cited in the plan","Search for 'SKILL.md cross-provider open standard' returns no results in the repo"],"finding":"The plan claims SKILL.md is 'now a cross-provider open standard' to justify de-branding the example skills from `claude-skills/`. The repo traces SKILL.md to `obra/superpowers` (a single personal GitHub repo cited in docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md), which is not a standards body. No specification URL, governance document, or evidence of multi-vendor adoption is cited.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f763995329e7d5fed","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Locked decisions (design session) — 'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-provider open standard)'","norm_id":"nf5d7010780cfdf01","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["SKILL.md is a useful format convention but not a ratified standard — calling it one overstates the justification for keeping it vs. adopting a different portable format","If 'cross-provider open standard' is inaccurate, the renaming from claude-skills/ loses its grounding and the de-branding decision needs a different justification"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Replace 'now a cross-provider open standard' with 'an established community convention (originated by obra/superpowers, referenced in docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md §2)' — this is both accurate and still supports the de-branding decision.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Name the specific `docs/` file (e.g. `docs/agent-guidance.md`) that serves as the authoritative source for `templates/AGENTS.md`, and reference it explicitly in the drift-guard AC's proving command.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["E2","F1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source' — no file path given","'push the portable rebar-usage guidance into docs/ as the single source of truth' — no specific docs/ file named","ABSENCE: no docs/ target file is named anywhere in the plan"],"finding":"The 'authoritative source' that `templates/AGENTS.md` must stay in sync with is never named. The AC says 'a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source' but the specific docs/ file (or set of files) serving as the source of truth is not identified, making the drift test unimplementable without a clarifying decision.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa7a0d5b3d1b07daa","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — `templates/AGENTS.md` bullet; Success Criteria — 'push portable rebar-usage guidance into docs/ as the single source of truth'","norm_id":"nc828de0f77cd6c81","priority":0.055,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An executing agent writes a drift test but must guess which docs/ file to diff against — different agents will make different choices, producing an inconsistent result.","A future maintainer cannot tell what file to update when the template drifts."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add to the AC: 'Proving: `diff <(grep -v '^#.*rebar-internal' docs/agent-guidance.md) templates/AGENTS.md` exits 0' (substituting the actual chosen file path).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.125,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Either enumerate the child stories inline (with titles/IDs) or add a link to the tracked child-story list so an executor can verify completeness without leaving the plan.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["E2","F1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'All child stories are closed and their changes are landed on main' — no child stories listed or linked","ABSENCE: no story list, no links to child tickets, no description of what work they cover"],"finding":"Child stories are referenced in the first AC ('All child stories are closed') but are not enumerated anywhere in the plan. An executing agent cannot know the full set of child stories, their scope, or how to verify completeness, making this AC unexecutable as written.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f73bf29f7daf820cd","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — 'All child stories are closed and their changes are landed on main'","norm_id":"n90cf4ded6002a285","priority":0.0629,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An agent treating this as a self-contained plan has no way to enumerate or close child stories.","A reviewer cannot determine whether 'all' child stories is 2 or 20."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a reference (URL or local file path) to the SKILL.md specification in the plan, and optionally add a lint step to the proving command that validates skills against it.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-provider open standard)' — no link or file reference to the SKILL.md specification","The AC's proving command (`rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l`) checks renaming only, not format compliance"],"finding":"The SKILL.md format is described as 'a cross-provider open standard' that example skills must conform to, but no spec pointer (URL, file path, or inline schema) is provided. An executor cannot verify SKILL.md compliance or know what the format requires.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f751e9b45c9ff5fe9","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Locked decisions — 'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-provider open standard)'","norm_id":"n912c99a36d9bcc9b","priority":0.1257,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An executor renames and de-brands skills but formats them incorrectly because the SKILL.md schema is unknown.","A linter or reviewer flags skills that don't match the spec, but there's no reference to consult."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (with proof command) covering CLAUDE.local.md: either verify it contains only machine/operator-local content (e.g. line-count or grep for known moved rules) or explicitly document its final state.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'CLAUDE.local.md mixes genuinely machine/operator-local content with generally-applicable project rules copied from CLAUDE.md'","Success Criteria: 'every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home in AGENTS.md or docs/'","No AC mentions CLAUDE.local.md or provides a proof command for it"],"finding":"CLAUDE.local.md cleanup is described as an in-scope deliverable (Context identifies it as mixing machine-local and generally-applicable content; Success Criteria explicitly names it: 'every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home') but no AC verifies either its remediation or its final state.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa53a168e04fab4e6","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Success Criteria paragraph 4 / Acceptance Criteria (all ACs)","norm_id":"na3ae3e99716e4589","priority":0.1571,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Implementer cleans up CLAUDE.md correctly but forgets CLAUDE.local.md; plan passes all ACs while CLAUDE.local.md still contains duplicated, generally-applicable rules that should have moved to docs/."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add an AC such as: 'CLAUDE.local.md retains only machine-local or operator-local overrides; no rule that belongs in AGENTS.md or docs/ remains there. Proving: diff the rules listed in CLAUDE.local.md against AGENTS.md/docs/ to confirm all general rules have a canonical home.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Strengthen AC2's proof step to verify that CLAUDE.md is lean after migration (e.g. add a line-count assertion such as `wc -l < CLAUDE.md | awk '$1 <= 30'` or equivalent threshold), confirming the removal side of the migration.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC2 proof: 'test -f AGENTS.md && rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md'","Context: 'CLAUDE.md is 665 lines and duplicates large parts of docs/'","Locked Decisions: 'a thin CLAUDE.md bridges Claude Code via a one-line @AGENTS.md import'","No line-count or content-removal check in AC2"],"finding":"The AC2 proof command (`rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md`) only confirms that an @AGENTS.md import line exists in CLAUDE.md; it does not verify that the previously-duplicated bulk content was actually removed, so a CLAUDE.md that still contains all 665 lines plus one import line would pass the criterion. The migration's 'removal' side is unverified.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8880d7e0ab44ca17","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC2 proof step","norm_id":"n9ac54d004463af1e","priority":0.11,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An implementer adds @AGENTS.md import at the top of CLAUDE.md without pruning the existing content; AC2 passes while the file is still 665 lines and full of duplicates."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Append to AC2's proof: `&& awk 'END{exit (NR > 30)}' CLAUDE.md` (or a similarly small threshold appropriate for 'thin pointer plus only Claude-only notes').","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (or extend an existing one) that verifies at least one proxy for 'no guidance lost' in docs/ — for example, a checklist of rule sections that must exist in docs/ files, or a test that cross-references AGENTS.md pointers against actual docs/ targets.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Scope: 'In: the root guidance files, docs/ homes for CLAUDE.md-native content, the .codex/.agents shims, examples/ skills, a client template + drift test, and a repo-wide reference sweep'","Success Criteria: 'duplicates no doc that already has an authoritative version'","No AC tests for the presence of newly-created or updated docs/ files"],"finding":"The docs/ migration — described in Scope ('In: docs/ homes for CLAUDE.md-native content') and Success Criteria ('duplicates no doc that already has an authoritative version') — has no covering AC to prove that formerly CLAUDE.md-native content arrived in docs/ with an authoritative home.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7063c2df4c4f578c","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section ('In:' list) / Acceptance Criteria (all ACs)","norm_id":"n20405d6479931f16","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Implementer writes a lean AGENTS.md by simply deleting previously-documented rules without creating the corresponding docs/ homes; all ACs pass but guidance is silently lost, violating the 'no guidance lost' success criterion."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit rollback/back-out plan (e.g., 'keep CLAUDE.md backup branch', expand-contract sequence, or a staged cut-over with a defined revert step) for the destructive CLAUDE.md replacement and examples/claude-skills rename.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["The plan describes replacing CLAUDE.md (665 lines) with a thin pointer and renaming examples/claude-skills, but lists only forward-proof ACs with no rollback steps.","T4 rubric: 'The remedy for a destructive/breaking change is an explicit ROLLBACK / back-out plan or expand-contract sequencing — checking only that breakage is acknowledged is insufficient; require the reversibility mechanism.'","ABSENCE: No 'rollback plan', 'revert', 'back-out', or staged-migration section appears anywhere in the plan."],"finding":"The plan acknowledges destructive steps (CLAUDE.md bulk deletion, examples/claude-skills rename) but provides no rollback/back-out plan or expand-contract sequencing for the migration. If mid-migration something goes wrong (e.g., the @AGENTS.md import fails in a Claude Code version, or content is mis-classified), there is no described path to revert.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb0988d7d6fa1b114","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria / Success Criteria","norm_id":"n6c3979aeb0f2c32a","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["The @AGENTS.md import syntax is not supported in an older Claude Code version used by a team member, leaving them with no guidance — but CLAUDE.md is already stripped.","Content is accidentally omitted during the CLAUDE.md → docs/ migration; without a staged approach or a snapshot, the loss is not caught until after the original is gone."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a 'Migration Safety' section: (1) tag the pre-migration state as a git ref; (2) land AGENTS.md and templates/ additively first (expand), verify all harnesses pick it up, then (3) thin CLAUDE.md and rename examples/ (contract). Document the revert command (`git revert <sha-range>`) explicitly.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit step (or AC) to update/remove the 'migrate CLAUDE.md' shim comment in `.codex/config.toml` once migration is complete.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Context explicitly names '.codex/config.toml with a \"migrate CLAUDE.md\" shim comment' as a pre-existing partial migration artifact.","ABSENCE: The Scope section and ACs contain no step or AC to update or remove this stale shim comment after migration.","Post-migration, a TODO referencing a migration that is complete is a stranded/misleading reference."],"finding":"The `.codex/config.toml` file contains a 'migrate CLAUDE.md' shim comment (called out in Context as existing) that will be semantically stale after migration completes, but the plan has no step to clean it up or update it.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8a530b10da2dcc3a","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Context section: '`.codex/config.toml` with a \"migrate CLAUDE.md\" shim comment'","norm_id":"n7f32bd50fe88ab52","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A contributor reads .codex/config.toml post-migration, sees a 'migrate CLAUDE.md' comment, and spends time investigating whether migration is still needed — it already happened."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to ACs: `rg 'migrate CLAUDE.md' .codex/config.toml | wc -l` returns 0 (or the comment is updated to reflect the completed state).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.125,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC proving command that asserts `AGENTS.md` stays within the target line count, e.g., `[ $(wc -l < AGENTS.md) -le 200 ]`, and wire it into `make lint` or `make test`.","cohort":["E3","F4"],"criteria":["E3","F4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'The root guidance file is lean (target ≤ ~200 lines) and duplicates no doc that already has an authoritative version' — stated as a success criterion","ABSENCE: No AC proving command checks line count of AGENTS.md"],"finding":"The ≤~200 lines target for the root guidance file is stated in Success Criteria but has no corresponding AC proving command, so it cannot be automatically verified.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0a0b0507e3a77f32","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Success Criteria (2nd bullet: 'The root guidance file is lean (target ≤ ~200 lines)') / Acceptance Criteria section","norm_id":"n98c160725f5c8c8d","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["AGENTS.md grows beyond 200 lines during migration as content is added; no gate fails, and the anti-bloat goal is quietly violated."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to the existing AC block: `Proving: [ $(wc -l < AGENTS.md) -le 200 ]` and add a corresponding `make` rule or CI step.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Name the specific `docs/` file (e.g. `docs/agent-guidance.md`) that serves as the authoritative source for `templates/AGENTS.md`, reference it in the drift-guard AC's proving command, and ensure the new test mirrors the `test_skill_shared_sync.py` pattern by hardcoding that path.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source' — no file path given anywhere in the plan","The existing `test_skill_shared_sync.py` pattern works precisely because it names an explicit canonical path (`SKILLS_DIR / 'shared' / 'test-design.md'`) — the drift test for `templates/AGENTS.md` needs the same specificity","ABSENCE: no `docs/` target file is named anywhere in the plan as the authoritative source for the client template","Prior plan-review cache (`.rebar/cache/plan-review/81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653/0a3e99a376cc6158b3fd.json`) independently flagged this same gap under E2/F1"],"finding":"The drift-guard mechanism for `templates/AGENTS.md` has an unresolved data-flow gap: the plan proposes 'a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source' but never names which specific file (or derived excerpt) in `docs/` is that authoritative source. The test cannot be written without this decision — an implementer must guess, and different agents will make different choices.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f5da2a39c8ef85627","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — `templates/AGENTS.md` bullet; Context paragraph — 'push the portable rebar-usage guidance into docs/ as the single source of truth'","norm_id":"n3f2e732921de809b","priority":0.055,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An executing agent writes the drift test but must invent the authoritative path — two agents working in parallel write incompatible tests against different files, and both pass `make test`.","The authoritative source in `docs/` is later edited but maintainers don't know which test to check, since no file was recorded as the canonical end of the sync relationship."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence to the `templates/AGENTS.md` AC bullet: 'The authoritative source is `docs/agent-guidance.md` (the portable rebar-usage guidance doc created in this epic); the drift test asserts byte-identity or structural equivalence between `templates/AGENTS.md` and that file. Proving: `python tests/unit/test_template_agents_sync.py` (modeled on `test_skill_shared_sync.py`).' Adjust the file name to match whatever `docs/` file the plan creates.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.125,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Confirm the child story that renames `examples/claude-skills/` explicitly covers updating `tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py` (hardcoded `SKILLS_DIR` path on line 26) and `examples/claude-skills/README.md` (hardcoded cp one-liner on line 44), so `make test` passes and `rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l` returns 0.","cohort":["T3"],"criteria":["T3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC3: 'make lint && make test pass on the merged result'","AC3 proof: `rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l` returns 0 (requires full rename)","test_skill_shared_sync.py line 26: `SKILLS_DIR = REPO_ROOT / 'examples' / 'claude-skills'`","test_skill_shared_sync.py line 27: `CANONICAL = SKILLS_DIR / 'shared' / 'test-design.md'`","If the directory is renamed to e.g. `examples/skills`, `CANONICAL.is_file()` returns False and `test_canonical_file_exists` fails immediately"],"finding":"`tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py` hardcodes `SKILLS_DIR = REPO_ROOT / 'examples' / 'claude-skills'` (line 26) and `CANONICAL = SKILLS_DIR / 'shared' / 'test-design.md'` — renaming the directory as required by AC3 without updating this test causes `make test` to fail, contradicting the plan's own proof command (`make lint && make test` passes).","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6a9197c71ab31ea1","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria #3 / tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py line 26","norm_id":"ne759fa2eea09159d","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A child story renames `examples/claude-skills/` but does not update `test_skill_shared_sync.py` — `make test` fails, blocking the epic's AC3 proof.","The AC3 proof command `rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l` counts `test_skill_shared_sync.py` itself as a match, so the count is never 0 until the test is also updated."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to the rename story's Acceptance Criteria: '`tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py` updated to reference the new directory path, and `make test` passes with the new path.' Also update the sync one-liner in `examples/<new-name>/README.md`.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Cite the Claude Code documentation URL for the `@file` import directive's path-resolution contract, and augment the AC2 proof with at least a spot-check command (e.g. `claude --print '@AGENTS.md'` or equivalent) or a note in the story confirming the resolution semantics were empirically verified.","cohort":["T3"],"criteria":["T3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC2 proof: `test -f AGENTS.md && rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md`","No existing usage of `@<file>` include syntax found anywhere in the repo's CLAUDE.md or tests","docs/session-id-shims.md references `code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks` but no `@` import docs are cited","Evidence class: Partially-verified — Claude Code does have an `@` include feature per general knowledge, but the specific path-resolution contract (is it relative to the file, to CWD, to repo root?) is UNVERIFIED in this codebase"],"finding":"The AC2 proof command `rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md` only verifies that the literal string `@AGENTS.md` is present in CLAUDE.md — it does not verify that Claude Code's `@file` import directive actually resolves `AGENTS.md` at the repo root. The specific path-resolution semantics of Claude Code's `@` include (relative to CLAUDE.md's location, or relative to CWD, or absolute?) are not cited or tested anywhere in the repo, leaving a gap between the string-presence proof and actual harness behaviour.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f06a72ca59c1eb5a8","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria #2 — Proving: `rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md`","norm_id":"n9f294aae1bd46708","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Claude Code resolves `@AGENTS.md` relative to CWD rather than relative to CLAUDE.md — works when invoked from repo root but silently fails in subdirectory sessions.","A future Claude Code version changes the `@` import mechanism — the string-presence proof still passes but the import stops working, with no test catching the regression."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Name the specific authoritative source file that `templates/AGENTS.md` must stay in sync with (or define the sync relationship: e.g., 'subset of AGENTS.md §X' or 'mirrors docs/Y.md'), so the drift-guard test can be written with an unambiguous canonical path.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC text: 'templates/AGENTS.md (client-usable, provider-neutral) exists and a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source'","Absence: no plan section names the authoritative source file (a docs/ page? a section of AGENTS.md itself?)","Contrast: test_skill_shared_sync.py line 25-26 shows the existing pattern: CANONICAL = SKILLS_DIR / 'shared' / 'test-design.md' — explicit, unambiguous"],"finding":"The drift-guard AC for `templates/AGENTS.md` references 'the authoritative source' but never names what file that is. Unlike the existing `test_skill_shared_sync.py` (which explicitly hardcodes `CANONICAL = SKILLS_DIR / 'shared' / 'test-design.md'`), the plan gives no analogous specification — an executor implementing the new drift-guard test cannot write it without knowing which file is the canonical half of the sync pair.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3b0d825d4c6b7102","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — bullet 2: 'a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source'","norm_id":"n729b668940670d4b","priority":0.055,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Executor writes a drift-guard test but picks the wrong canonical end (e.g., AGENTS.md root vs. a docs/ subsection), silently testing the wrong sync relationship.","The drift-guard test passes vacuously if both files are always written together, masking real drift."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add to AC bullet 2: '...in sync with `<path/to/canonical.md>` (the authoritative source)' and ensure the implementing story specifies the same path in its own AC.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.125,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Provide a reference (URL or internal doc) for the SKILL.md cross-provider standard's required fields/structure, so the generalization step has a compliance target.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-provider open standard)'","Absence: no URL, governance body, required-fields list, or spec document is cited anywhere in the plan","The existing SKILL.md files (tool-verified: examples/claude-skills/rebar-brainstorm/SKILL.md) contain a YAML front-matter `description` field plus free-form markdown — but whether this matches the cross-provider standard or needs structural change is unspecified"],"finding":"The plan calls SKILL.md 'now a cross-provider open standard' and directs the executor to de-brand and generalize the existing skill files to that standard, but provides no pointer to the standard's spec, field vocabulary, or structural requirements. An executor cannot verify compliance without knowing what the format mandates.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f140a8e542efce31d","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Locked decisions paragraph: 'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-provider open standard) but are de-branded and generalized.'","norm_id":"nd49b1ece5caafdcb","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Executor generalizes skills by removing Claude branding but leaves format unchanged — possibly compliant, possibly not, with no way to verify.","A future provider's harness expects a different required field (e.g., `name`, `version`, `tools`) that the generalized SKILL.md omits, silently failing to load."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit step specifying that `tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py` (and any other files hardcoding `examples/claude-skills/`) must be updated as part of the rename story, and clarify whether the AC prove command should exclude test/source files from its count.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC prove command: `rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l` returns 0","tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py line 25: `SKILLS_DIR = REPO_ROOT / 'examples' / 'claude-skills'`","tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py line 10: `cp examples/claude-skills/shared/test-design.md \\`","No plan section specifies that test_skill_shared_sync.py must be updated to reflect the new path after rename"],"finding":"The AC prove command `rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l` returns 0 is the end-state check for the skills rename, but `tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py` hardcodes `SKILLS_DIR = REPO_ROOT / 'examples' / 'claude-skills'` (tool-verified). The plan provides no protocol for how this test file gets updated on rename — leaving the AC's own proving command in a broken state unless the test is also updated, yet no story or step mentions it.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f985a82580fa15293","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — bullet 3 prove command: `rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l` returns 0","norm_id":"n6d2f31e713e82478","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Executor renames examples/claude-skills/ to examples/skills/ (or similar) and verifies the AC prove command passes — but test_skill_shared_sync.py now points to a missing directory, breaking `make test`.","Alternatively, the test is updated but the prove command now counts the test file itself as a stale reference, causing the AC to incorrectly report failure."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Update the AC prove command to `rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . --glob '!tests/' --glob '!*.py' | wc -l` and add 'update test_skill_shared_sync.py path constants' to the rename story's task list.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Identify the two stowaway Session-log topics in CLAUDE.md by name and confirm each has a specific home in S1/073d's docs additions (or explicitly assign them to a child that will home them).","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"the two 'stowaway' topics currently mixed into CLAUDE.md's Session-logs heading are simply not carried into AGENTS.md\" (S2 What section)","Parent SC4: 'No guidance is lost in the move — every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home in AGENTS.md or docs/'","S1/073d adds session_log section to event-schema.md and auto-rotation to user-guide.md, but the cross-reference to the stowaways is implicit — neither story names the specific stowaway topics or confirms they map to those additions","container pairing: parent + 064f-0484-2795-4ac7/073d-51d8-3e58-4b14/1d75-89cb-f37e-482e/46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508/5b01-add0-e970-44bd/6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4/955c-7a98-2485-4209"],"finding":"Child 6642 explicitly states two 'stowaway topics' currently mixed into CLAUDE.md's Session-logs heading are 'simply not carried into AGENTS.md,' without naming the destination. This is a partial-without-remainder pattern against parent SC4 ('no guidance is lost'). If S1/073d's additions to event-schema.md and user-guide.md do not precisely cover these stowaways, the content is silently dropped with no child owning the gap.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6facbd38bf4580e3","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4","norm_id":"n61df83b65849bcaf","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["If the stowaways are edge-case semantics not captured by S1's 'session_log ticket type' section or 'auto-rotation' paragraph, they disappear from guidance permanently with no CI check to detect the loss."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In child 6642, name the two stowaway topics explicitly and add a cross-reference to the S1/073d section that homes each one, making the coverage verifiable during review.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Formalize the prose dependency in child 46f8 as a tracked depends_on link to child 6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"Depends on: the AGENTS.md story (so the CLAUDE.md → AGENTS.md reference repoint targets the real new file)\" — prose only, in the Scope section","No 'depends_on' metadata field mentioned in the ticket body","Child 6642 creates AGENTS.md; child 46f8 repoints skill CLAUDE.md references to AGENTS.md","container pairing: parent + 064f-0484-2795-4ac7/073d-51d8-3e58-4b14/1d75-89cb-f37e-482e/46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508/5b01-add0-e970-44bd/6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4/955c-7a98-2485-4209"],"finding":"Child 46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508 states it 'Depends on: the AGENTS.md story' (6642) so that repointed AGENTS.md references target a real file, but this dependency is expressed only as prose — no formal depends_on link is mentioned. If 46f8 lands before 6642 creates AGENTS.md, skill bodies and the README would reference a non-existent file, breaking 'make lint && make test.'","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f39d063311a9ae3b0","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508","norm_id":"n2490eb5b0dbddf96","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:cited-reference-inaccurate","scenarios":["46f8 is picked up and merged before 6642; linters or tests that validate linked files fail because AGENTS.md does not yet exist in the repo."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add `depends_on: [6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4]` to child 46f8's ticket metadata (matching the pattern used by 064f and 6642 for their S1 dependency).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"no","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a CONTRIBUTING.md note or migration notice (within S3/955c or S6/5b01) instructing team members to trim their own CLAUDE.local.md to operator-local content only, and specifying what belongs there.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["CLAUDE.local.md is git-ignored and operator-local by design","S3/955c scope: 'CLAUDE.local.md only (git-ignored, local)'","Parent SC4: 'No guidance is lost in the move' — but each developer's local copy of the duplicated rules is silently unaddressed","No child provides any communication artifact (e.g., a CONTRIBUTING.md note, migration notice, or team announcement) to prompt other developers to remediate their local files","container pairing: parent + 064f-0484-2795-4ac7/073d-51d8-3e58-4b14/1d75-89cb-f37e-482e/46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508/5b01-add0-e970-44bd/6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4/955c-7a98-2485-4209"],"finding":"Child 955c-7a98-2485-4209 (CLAUDE.local.md remediation) affects only the current operator's local file. In a team environment, other developers may have their own git-ignored CLAUDE.local.md files containing the same duplicated project-workflow rules that the parent SC4 and this child aim to eliminate. No child addresses propagation to other team members, leaving a consumer-impact gap for multi-developer teams.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ffd377a2886ef0137","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 955c-7a98-2485-4209","norm_id":"nd628cc7971e31b6d","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A team member with an old CLAUDE.local.md continues to have Claude Code read duplicated/stale project rules alongside the new AGENTS.md guidance, causing inconsistent agent behavior across the team."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In child 955c, add an AC requiring a committed doc or CONTRIBUTING.md addition that tells other developers how to migrate their CLAUDE.local.md, so the team-wide consumer impact is addressed.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G3","G4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The canonical source file for 064f's drift-guard delimited region is unresolved: the de-risking text offers 'docs/ticket-model.md plus the workflow loop authored in S1, or a dedicated docs/_shared/rebar-usage.md' as alternatives but does not commit to one. 073d's refined plan scatters content across four separate doc files (docs/ticket-model.md, docs/concurrency.md, docs/event-schema.md, docs/user-guide.md); none of these individually contains all the 'portable rebar-usage' prose that the drift-guard needs to compare byte-for-byte. Without a single canonical source file, 064f's test cannot be implemented as designed (byte-identical delimited region), and 073d has no obligation to produce that single source. This is a partial-without-remainder gap: 064f covers AC3 only IF a single consolidated source exists, but no child commits to producing one.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc780fc99f7979fa7","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 064f-0484-2795-4ac7 — De-risking results / Revised AC; child 073d-51d8-3e58-4b14 — Refined plan","norm_id":"n352202c3bcbeb2e9","priority":0.11,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add docs/_shared/rebar-usage.md to 073d's scope as a thin aggregation file (just assembles the portable rebar-usage sections with include-markers); update 064f to treat that file as the sole canonical source for the drift-guard byte comparison. This mirrors how test_skill_shared_sync.py treats shared/ today.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","